						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- set up the IRQ counter as soon as NMI happens, and SEI</div>Be careful. Returning from the NMI will restore the previous flags so you'll need something like:<div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">PLA<br />ORA #$04<br />PHA</div>Assuming that you haven't actually pushed anything yet (i.e. saved the registers on the stack), otherwise you'll have to play with the stack pointer..
<br />
<br />Or perhaps a simple PLP/SEI/PHP sequence would do, but this is presumably done because of spurious IRQs triggered for some reason so perhaps that might happen here too.</div>

